&gt; Hi Markus,
&gt; 
&gt; link relation type definition are not (RDF) property definitions. Where
&gt; the latter ones define something about the properties (relations) it
&gt; themselves, the former ones include something about the processing of
&gt; these relations, i.e., how to handle the referred object.
&gt; To sum up, link relation type definitions are usually orthogonal to
&gt; (RDF) property definitions. See also, e.g., [1] for a detailed
&gt; discussion on this issue and related ones.
&gt; 
&gt; Cheers,
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; Bo
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; [1] http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/rest-discuss/message/17242
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; On 1/8/2012 1:17 PM, Markus Lanthaler wrote:
&gt; &gt; Hi,
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Why do you think JSON-LD doesn&#39;t utilize link relations? They are
&gt; just more
&gt; &gt; terse. Let&#39;s look at an example:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; {
&gt; &gt; &quot;@context&quot;: {
&gt; &gt; &quot;homepage&quot;: { &quot;@id&quot;: http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/homepage&quot;, &quot;@type&quot;:
&gt; &quot;@id&quot;
&gt; &gt; }
&gt; &gt; }
&gt; &gt; },
&gt; &gt; &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Markus Lanthaler&quot;,
&gt; &gt; &quot;homepage&quot;: &quot;http://www.markus-lanthaler.com/&quot;
&gt; &gt; }
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; This (incomplete) JSON-LD document would tell you that there&#39;s a JSON
&gt; object
&gt; &gt; which has a key &quot;homepage&quot; that represents a homepage according to
&gt; the FOAF
&gt; &gt; vocabulary - that&#39;s the rel part, isn&#39;t it!? The value of it is
&gt; &gt; &quot;http://www.markus-lanthaler.com/&quot;. The coercion in the context tells
&gt; a
&gt; &gt; JSON-LD parser that it is an IRI and not just a string and thus
&gt; allows a
&gt; &gt; client to follow that link.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; See also Manu Sporny&#39;s comment on Mark Notthingsham&#39;s blog post about
&gt; &gt; &quot;Linking in JSON&quot; [1]. I think there is still some confusion about
&gt; what
&gt; &gt; JSON-LD is (intended to be).
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; [1] http://www.mnot.net/blog/2011/11/25/linking_in_json#comment-1737
&gt; &gt;
