&gt; &gt;  &gt; relation types (as it is the same problem with all RDF
&gt; serialisation
&gt; &gt;  &gt; formats ATM). In contrast, HAL makes use of link relations types
&gt; &gt;  &gt; (&quot;href&quot;, ...), and, hence, supports the HATEOAS constraint of
&gt; REST.
&gt; &gt;  &gt; So my solution proposal for this problem still is to design a
&gt; &gt;  &gt; vocabulary
&gt; &gt;  &gt; to describe link relation type definitions in a machine
&gt; processable way
&gt; &gt;  &gt; and attach these definitions to our well-known RDF property
&gt; &gt;  &gt; definitions,
&gt; &gt;  &gt; i.e., then we have knowledge about the property (relation) itself
&gt; and
&gt; &gt;  &gt; how it can be processed by a client.
